{"id":37620,"date":"2022-01-10T12:24:47","date_gmt":"2022-01-10T08:24:47","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=37620"},"modified":"2025-02-25T11:45:02","modified_gmt":"2025-02-25T07:45:02","slug":"reciting-one-ayah","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2022\/01\/10\/reciting-one-ayah\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Prayer: The Prophet spends all night reciting one verse"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>Abu Dharr reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, prayed at night reciting a single verse until morning, by which he would bow and prostrate, \u201c<strong>If You punish them, they are Your servants. If You forgive them, You are the Almighty, the Wise,<\/strong>\u201d (5:118). When the Prophet awoke in the morning, I said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, you continued to recite this verse until morning, bowing and prostrating by it.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Verily, I asked my Lord for the intercession of my nation and He gave it to me. It will be granted, if Allah wills, to whoever does not associate anything with Allah.<\/strong>\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: Musnad Ah\u0323mad 21328<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <em>Hasan<\/em> (fair) according to Al-Arna\u2019ut<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0630\u064e\u0631\u064d\u0651 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0645\u064e \u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0629\u064b \u0641\u064e\u0642\u064e\u0631\u064e\u0623\u064e \u0628\u0650\u0622\u064a\u064e\u0629\u064d \u062d\u064e\u062a\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u0628\u064e\u062d\u064e \u064a\u064e\u0631\u0652\u0643\u064e\u0639\u06